title: How Jiffy Lube Performs a Signature Service Oil Change, presented by Jiffy Lube
description:
Learn more about the Jiffy Lube Signature Service Oil Change at: https://www.jiffylube.com/auto-services/oil-change

Find Jiffy Lube locations near you: https://www.jiffylube.com/locations

The Jiffy Lube Signature Service Oil Change is a lot more than your regular oil change. We inspect, check/fill and clean essential components of your vehicle too. Basically, we make sure you car is running smoothly so you can Leave Worry Behind.

Upon arrival, you’ll our service bays and highly trained Jiffy Lube technicians ready to service your bay. Depending on the size of the location and time of the day, the team could vary from three to seven employees.

Carefully follow the direction of the technician to pull your vehicle into the bay. Our technicians above and below get to work as soon as the car is stopped. The technician under the bay will drain fluids and replace the oil filter while other technicians get pushing checking your oil level, transmission fluid, differential fluid, transfer case fluid, power steering fluid, windshield washer fluid, and battery water. They’ll also give a look over your brake fluid levels, serpentine belts, wiper blades, antifreeze levels, engine and passenger air filters, headlights, and the chassis.

You’ll hear technicians above and below the bay calling out their progress to each other during the process. That’s to ensure the proper steps are taken to service your vehicle the right way.

Once your car is filled with fresh oil and all of your systems have been checked, a courtesy technician will wash exterior windows and vacuum the interior floorboards.

As we said, the Jiffy Lube Signature Service Oil Change isn’t just an oil change, it is preventive maintenance to keep your vehicle running smoothly. We help get you in and out quickly so you can take back your day and Leave Worry Behind.

Download Jiffy Lube coupons and promotions: https://www.jiffylube.com/coupons

Watch more How-To videos in our Check and Change series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL-5Ed_M7rD80-_oD5WZGmwETrN94kZFC_

title: Most Luxurious Limousines In The World
description:

You’ve seen VTEC on cars, but what does VTEC mean?  VTEC has to do with the valves in your engine that help dictate airflow, horsepower and fuel consumption.  This Science Garage gets into Cams, lobes, lifters and more before narrowing in on how VTEC works.  Cars have single cams, overhead cams, dual overhead cams and even triple overhead cams to help them do their jobs. title: Mega Tow Trucks - The World's Toughest Towing Vehicles | Full Documentary
description:
1000 tons in tow - They tow busses down the highway and haul heavy military equipment through the forest. They move the world’s largest aircraft, recover tanks from war zones, and haul enormous launch vehicles. these heavy-duty transporters are among the most powerful towing and recovery vehicles in the world. These tow trucks often transport 30 times their own weight – and the loads they carry are huge. These specialty vehicles are called into action when exceptionally heavy loads need to be transported or recovered. Their missions are often dangerous ones – so safety is a top priority.

title: ANTI-LAG | How it Works
description:
Turbos are great! But that boost comes after some lag while the turbo spools up. Some high performance cars are equipped with ANTILAG systems to keep those turbos spinning away! They pop and bang to keep their sweet sweet turbos spooled up! They’re the darlings of Drifting and Rally! We break down the two kinds of antilag systems you’re most likely to encounter, and we compare them with the also awesome two step rev limiting. All of them sound awesome and can shoot flames!

Why Cheap Cars Are Disappearing
description:
There are about 40 different car brands in the United States, but one kind of car that appears to be disappearing is the cheap car. Historically, about 20 percent of vehicle sales would have transacted below $20,000; however, they have completely dried up in the last few years. New cars are becoming more expensive, and it is unlikely those cheap cars will ever be back.

title: The Ford Ranger Unlimited Test Drive – No 11: The Farmer
description:
The Next-Gen Ranger is tougher, more versatile and more capable than ever before. And, to prove it, we sent one Ranger out on an epic 16,000 kilometre journey around the entire country, inviting 16 everyday Australians to see if the Ranger helps them to live a life without limits.

In this episode of the Ranger Unlimited Test Drive, farmer Rob puts the Ranger to work on the hills of his sheep farm.

We’d like to acknowledge the Traditional Custodians of the lands on which we filmed this campaign. We pay our respects to Elders past and present, and extend that respect to all
First Nations people, with special thanks to those from Countries: Eora, Dunghutti, Kabi Kabi, Jinibara, Kuku-yalanji, Yolngu, Larrakia, Yawuru, Jabirr Jabirr, Ngumbarl, Whadjuk, Nyoongar, Yuat, Wirangu, Peramangk, Kaurna, Bunganditj, Meintangk, Taungurong, Wurundjeri, Bunurong, Gunaikurnai, Darug and Darkinjung.

title: Trainz - Excursion Trains Race! Feat N&W 611, SP 4449, C&O 614, ATSF 2926, Southern 4501!
description:
Hello club members and visitors, welcome back!😀 One of our viewers suggested racing of excursion trains, so here you are! In part one, we adopted our viewer's suggestion, Southern #4501 double headed with N&W #1218 vs. N&W #611 double headed with Southern Pacific #4449. In part two, we have N&W #611 double headed with Southern Pacific #4449 vs. C&O #611 double headed with ATSF #2926! We used K&L Trainz Cotton Belt heavy excursion consist for both races to make it a little bit more challenging.    

We always welcome suggestions and ideas about our content, so please don't hesitate to leave us a message in the comment section! If you love what we have been doing, please subscribe to become a member of our club for free,  sharing, and👍like our videos to support us! Thank you for watching!  🤗

title: New Civic Type R: More power than AMG A35, M135i, S3 & Golf R!!
description:
Want to know how to sell your car? 83% of customers get a higher price with carwow - it’s also free and easy! Check us out here: https://bit.ly/Buy-Sell-WOW
.............................................................

Introducing the all-new Honda Civic Type R! 

It’s the 6th generation Type R, as well as the 25th anniversary of the very first Type R being released, and it’s time to find out if it’s the best hot Civic yet! 

So for starters, let’s take a look at the design. If anything this new Type R has been toned down compared to the 5th generation. Gone is the big bonnet scoop, instead replaced by a small vent. Speaking of vents, a number of fake ones found on the previous generation have also been removed, as have the stuck-on wheel arch extensions! All in all, it still looks great, even if it’s a bit less in your face than before. 

When it comes to performance, you’ll find the same 2-litre 4-cylinder turbo under the bonnet as before. Now, we don’t know the power figures just yet, but we do know that this will be the most powerful Type R yet! As a result, it’ll have more than 320hp, which makes it more powerful than a Golf R, Audi S3, BMW M135i and an AMG A35! 

On the inside, the new Type R is pretty similar to the standard Civic, although it’s got a number of exclusive upgrades including bright red sports seats, a different steering wheel, and of course, a shiny titanium gear stick! 

So what do you think, is this the best-looking Type R yet? Or should Honda have made it even wilder than the previous generation? Let us know in the COMMENTS!
